<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871117-0057 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Seaman Furniture Co.</HL><DD> 11/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SEAMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Kohlberg Kravis Roberts andamp; Co., New York, began a $26-a-share tender offer for as many as 10.5 million, or 77%, of Seaman Furniture Co.'s shares outstanding.    The leveraged buy-out offer for the Carle Place, N.Y.-based furniture retailer is valued at $354 million. Seaman family members hold about 5.9 million, or 43%, of the 13.6 million shares outstanding. They have granted Kohlberg Kravis, an investment banking concern, an option to buy their stake, valued at $153 million.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Seaman shares rose 12.5 cents to close at $23.    The offer is subject to Kohlberg Kravis receiving a majority of the shares outstanding and to completion of financing. In a leveraged buy-out, investors acquire a company largely with debt that ultimately is paid with funds generated by the acquired company's operations or the sale of its assets. The offer is due to expire at midnight EST Dec. 14. Salomon Brothers Inc. is dealer-manager. </TEXT></DOC>